g.text: 6. A new WAL Record is created and written
into the buffer at the location
7. Postgres adds a new WAL Record
to the WAL buffer, and then flushes all the
records from the buffer to the WAL segment fine
it to the storage (HDD or SSD).
When this parameter is on, the PostgreSQL server
writes the entire content of each disk page to WAL during
the first modification of that page after a checkpoint.
